    "#### List Comprehension:\n",
    "List comprehension is a Python feature to create new lists by transforming elements of an existing list. It’s particularly useful in business analysis for filtering or transforming large data sets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example of list comprehension\n",
    "squares = [x**2 for x in range(10)]\n",
    "print(squares)  # Outputs: [0, 1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81]"
   ]
  },
